【Easy Maintenance】The fake olive tree don’t need water, fertilizer or sunlight. No pruning. All you need to do is to clean the dust regularly. You don’t need to worry about the dead plants. Hands free and you can have a lasting lifelike olive tree.

【Good Wishes】Olive trees have always been symbol of peace, hope, vitality and victory. Decorate an artificial olive tree in your home and let good luck comes to you. Our faux olive trees also create a tropical, relaxing and happy atmosphere. Making your home warm and sweet, washing away the fatigue of your day after work.

【Perfect Home Decor】Do you always don’t know how to decorate your empty corner? Try these faux olive trees! They are perfect touch for the empty corner in your home, balcony, office, porch. They are also decorative outdoors like the area outside the door. They can be a gift for wedding, coming Christmas, etc.

【Easy to assemble】You will get two trunks after opening the package. Splice them and you will get a full fake olive tree! The branches are flexible so you can unfold them to the shape you like or fold them which is space-saving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've been wanting a faux olive tree for a while, but all of them were so incredibly expensive and I wasn't 100% sure I would like one in my home, so I wanted a reasonably priced one. This tree exceeded my expectations and I couldn't be happier with it. The tree was easy to assemble and after a little fluffing looks fantastic. I paired it with a woven basket and it's perfect.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A lovely alternative
reviews.reviewText: I love plants and wish I could have big live plants, but with a clowder of cats, that is nigh impossible. Our live little cacti have some defense, but even they suffer a bit. Most of our live plants must be hung out of reach. So, to have lots of greenery, we have turned to faux plants. They are safer for the cats since many larger plants are poisonous to our feline friends. This is a really lovely Monstera and looks almost real. The only thing that bothers me are the two stickers to show how the top is supposed to fit on the base. The stickers do not come off easily and I will have to use some adhesive remover to get them completely off. I don't think it was really necessary to have the stickers, but maybe some people would have trouble figuring out how the square peg fits the square hole. Oh well. It is a minor thing and not worth deducting any stars. I'd love to get an even taller one, eventually. Now to get some nice pots for my "plants".

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Poorly packaged, generically potted, decent plant
reviews.reviewText: This plant is okay but for the price, I wouldn't purchase it again. For starters, the whole thing is packaged completely loosely in the manufacturer's packaging. I'm not talking about Amazon's packaging, mind you, but the product manufacturer's. This allowed the plastic pot to break in transit, making it difficult to even stand up on its own. There is literally no packing material in the box with the plant at all. I found that quite strange. The stated height is true, however. The plant looks somewhat realistic once the two pieces are assembled and some bending of leaves and branches is completed. The pot, however...aside from being broken, it is undersized for the size of the plant and is very plain. I will have to "replant" this to a larger and more decorative pot to make good use of it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a really nice looking tree; I'm a former groundskeeper and horticulture lover and my wife is practically a dendrophile, so we expect a lot of artificial plants. The finish of the bark looks and feels real, and the branches and leaves look like they are real and growing naturally. The olives don't look great, but they don't stand out, either.Literally just one step to put together, top onto bottom and there are arrows on the trunk to line up to make it, somehow, even easier. Fluffing isn't too difficult, either, and the branches hold the shape you give them pretty well while being flexible enough to help make it look natural.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality Lifelike Tree
reviews.reviewText: This is a beautiful quality tree. It's large and I love it! It makes a statement in my room, while adding a relaxing warmth.The trunk and leaves are both very lifelike. It requires some spreading and primping, but I was very pleased to find the stems and leaves are thick and durable. I was able to really bend and spread without damaging or pulling the leaves off.Just add a pot! It arrives in a tiny black weighted pot that's way too small. It would be top-heavy to leave it standing alone like that. As soon as I placed it in a larger pot, it stood tall and it came to life. I'll probably add some moss or greenery at the bottom.You would never know this is a fake plant from just a few feet away.There are good fake and bad fakes - this is definitely a good one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love the look. The leaves are nice and I love the stalk. I love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Impressive, stable, looks great and well worth the price!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my office and everyone loves it! It comes in a nice package in 2 parts which are easy to assemble and the branches are easily adjustable unlike others that I have ordered in the past which are stiff and don't work with being adjusted...this plant does! It looks authentic, came in a nice box which was well packaged to avoid any possible damage and has a sturdy base. We did add a basket over the base to give it that "pop" which is shown in the last photo. We really like this addition to our office!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I put the fake olive tree at the door and got compliment from my neighbor. She asked me where I bought such a beautiful olive tree and I told her it was a fake tree. She was surprised at how realistic they look and asked me for the link!Besides, the fake tree is easy to assemble that we arranged it in only 20 mins!Great product. Would buy again.
